text: Alfred Pycock (12 May 1900 - 13 March 1964) was a British swimmer. He competed in the men's 100 metre freestyle event at the 1924 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1900 births Category:1964 deaths Category:British male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Great Britain Category:Swimmers at the 1924 Summer Olympics Category:People from Fulham Category:Sportspeople from London
